rves or contact COL Susan Hastings at 464 7607  Interlibrary Loan When Preston Library does not own an item that you need  you may obtain it from another library  There are no limits and no fees for this service  Logging on to the Interlibrary Loan system lets you place requests  check their status  and access the documents that have been received electronically  Additionally  while using electronic resources such as library databases and WorldCat  you may initiate an ILL request  For more information  contact Interlibrary Loan Manager  Media Services Media Services offers faculty training and consultation in the selection and use of multimedia software and hardware  Media equipment is also available for short term loans for presentations  Media Services Home Page Video about Media Services Contact MAJ Michael Brickler at 464 7655 Contact Ms  Cathy Wells at 464 7567 Library Hours Click here for library hours  Circulation Generous loan policies facilitate your academic endeavors  For details  see Circulation Information for Faculty or contact LTC Susan Hastings at 464 7607  Meeting Rooms Forms and policies  as well as information about meeting rooms at Preston Library  are available here  Reference and Instruction COL Janet Holly and MAJ Accacia Mullen for your Reference and Instruction needs   They are available to assist you with reference questions for your own work  they can also meet with your classes and students individually to assist them through the research process  Ordering Materials Each academic department is allocated a budget to order library materials  and we welcome your purchase requests The Book Order Request Form and the Serials Request Form are available online   Also  each department receives Choice cards with reviews of new scholarly titles  Contact your department head to learn how Choice cards are managed in your department  For details  see the Collection Development Policy   VMI Foundation Keydet Club Alumni Webcams Directories My VMI  RESO